'''Talon Squadron'''&mdash;also called '''Talon Squad'''&mdash;was a [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] [[X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wing]] [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] squadron formed shortly after the [[Battle of Thyferra]]. Commanded by Brevet [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Myn Donos]], it was dissolved after the [[Ambush at Gravan Seven]] in which eleven X-wing [[Pilot/Legends|pilots]] were [[Death/Legends|killed]] by [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Apwar Trigit]]'s forces.

==History==
Talon Squadron was one of a number of new [[X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wing]] [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] squadrons created by the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]]. It was commissioned following the creation of [[Gauntlet Squadron]], and prior to the formation of [[Wraith Squadron]]. All Talon [[Pilot/Legends|pilots]] were trained by [[Lieutenant/Legends|Lieutenants]] [[Derek Klivian/Legends|Derek Klivian]] and [[Wes Janson/Legends|Wes Janson]], veterans of [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Squadron]], and placed under the command of [[Lieutenant/Legends|Lieutenant]] [[Myn Donos]], a [[Corellian Bloodstripe|bloodstriped]] [[Corellian/Legends|Corellian]] pilot&mdash;then promoted to the rank of Brevet [[Captain/Legends|Captain]].

====Ambush====
{{Quote|Talon Squad is gone.''"<br />"''What do you mean, gone?''"<br />"''Wiped out. Ambush. Everyone is dead except Lieutenant Donos.|[[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]] and [[Derek Klivian/Legends|Derek "Hobbie" Klivian]]|<ref name="X-Wing: Wraith Squadron">''[[X-Wing: Wraith Squadron]]''</ref>}}
In the [[Gravan system/Legends|Gravan system]] on [[7 ABY/Legends|7 ABY]] (42:10:3),<ref name="Atlas" /> following what seemed like a lone [[TIE/IN interceptor/Legends|TIE Interceptor]] with no accompanying [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]]-capable ship&mdash;previously marked safe by a [[New Republic Intelligence Service|New Republic Intelligence]] operative who turned out to be the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial-trained]] and [[Zsinj]]-loyal [[Gara Petothel]]&mdash;Talon Squadron found themselves [[Ambush at Gravan Seven|ambushed]] over [[Gravan Seven]] by over three dozen [[TIE/ln space superiority starfighter/Legends|TIE starfighters]] sent by [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Apwar Trigit]]. Only Brevet Captain Myn Donos and "[[Talon Twelve]]" survived the initial volley of laser fire. After a short dogfight where Donos and "Talon Twelve" were pursued by a dozen TIE fighters each, Donos managing to shoot down three of them and "Talon Twelve"'s X-wing sustaining minor damage&mdash;the lone TIE Interceptor that led Talon Squadron into the trap appeared once more. Donos discovered on a close pass inspection that it was a member of the [[181st Imperial Fighter Wing/Legends|181st Imperial Fighter Group]]. The Interceptor pilot tried to get a targeting lock on "Talon Twelve" as Donos quickly tried to get behind. Both of them fired simultaneously. Donos' shot forced the Interceptor to disengage with damaged engines, but its shots landed hits on "Talon Twelve"'s X-wing causing it to break apart. "Talon Twelve" tried to eject, but her canopy initially jammed, prevented her from successfully escaping her doomed vessel. By the time her canopy broke loose, "Talon Twelve" was unconscious and her ejection seat shot into the side of a rift wall on the planet, killing her. With his whole squadron dead, Donos managed to survive the encounter and report back to his superiors, choosing to live only because he decided that he needed to inform the Talon Squadron members' families of the pilots' deaths.

====Dissolution====
{{Quote|I've just read the report from your last transmission. I wanted to congratulate you on the destruction of Talon Squadron.''"<br />"''Thank you. The code-slicer who planted the false information about the security of the Gravan system later reported that they have decommissioned Talon Squadron entirely."|[[Warlord/Legends|Warlord]] [[Zsinj]] and [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Apwar Trigit]]|<ref name="X-Wing: Wraith Squadron" />}}
The ambush at Graven Seven left Donos as the sole Talon Squadron survivor. With such heavy losses, Talon Squadron was decommissioned and Donos transferred to Wraith Squadron, losing his brevet rank and remaining a lieutenant.

==Behind the scenes==
In the WizKids' game, ''[[Star Wars PocketModel TCG: Base Set]]'', Donos' X-wing appears as a representation of Talon Squadron in the [[Star_Wars_PocketModel_TCG:_Base_Set#Imperial_Power-up_Pack|''Imperial Power-up Pack'']] promotional release.

